transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I noticed you guys came out with a new Viagra, and I'm signed up with you guys. I was just wondering how I could order that.

Speaker 1: Sure, I can help you out with that. Give me one second. Pull up your profile.

Speaker 2: I think it's AGB is what it is.

Speaker 1: Yeah. Christopher, can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: February 25, 1969.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much. I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: We have the AGB. It's the same price. The quantity of 10 is $63.95.

Speaker 2: Is that for a month's supply?

Speaker 1: Yeah, so it comes in a quantity of 10. Then we have 25 for $113.95, and then we have a quantity of 40 for $163.95.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'd like to just get the lower one. Just try it and see if it's going to work for me.

Speaker 1: Okay, 10.

Speaker 2: Is that 100 milligrams?

Speaker 1: Yeah, 100 milligrams. Okay, are we still using the Visa ending in 3187?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: All right, perfect.

Speaker 2: How early do you take it? Just take an hour to work it in?

Speaker 1: Yeah, just take it an hour prior, and try to take it on an empty stomach, or just don't eat a fatty meal like a burger or a steak, because that will affect the medication breakdown.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Do they keep sending them after that?

Speaker 1: Yeah, so they'll put you on automatic refills on a monthly basis, but you can change that now that you have the VIP status.

Speaker 2: You can change it to every two months, every three months, every four months.

Speaker 1: A lot of people just like to go ahead and put a six-month hold on it. That way it keeps your prescription active.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that way I could try it and see. Then I just call back and tell them if I want more.

Speaker 1: Yeah, okay. I'll go ahead and pause you until May 1st.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, perfect.

Speaker 2: I just want to make sure it's going to work.

Speaker 1: Yeah, not a problem. Perfect. You're all set.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, have a good day.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Bye.
